summary: revengingbarnes writing challenge / theme: TV shows
title: revengingbarnes writing challenge / theme: TV shows
excerpt: All the prompts are TV shows to be used as AUs! I would love for as many people to participate as possible, and i hope this will be as fun for you to write as it will be for me to read xx Here we go! Let me explain: You can use the tv show as inspiration, can fit your character into one of the show’s characters, follow the storyline, or not at all! It’s all up to you. Whatever you want to do within the confines of that universe. So go crazy!
description:
YO, someone please take the Brooklyn 99 prompt so I can read Bucky & Rosa being best friends??? 

Or Gilmore Girls because OMG, I don’t think Steve or Bucky could possibly keep up with how fast Lorelei and Rory talk, but I bet Scott Lang could! LOL I don’t know why, I’m just convinced. I think he and Hope would fit into Stars Hollow quite nicely :) 

Unfortunately, Scott & Hope aren’t on the list of characters that can be in the fics. BUT OMG LANCE TUCKER IS, I’d KILL to see Lance Tucker in Stars Hollow!!! I feel like he’d be spun around and upside down!

Honestly, if you know of someone who takes B99 or GG challenge, please let me know cuz I’ll be SO excited to read it!

summary: Requested by @eater-of-hopes-and-dreams “All right, let’s get this over with,” your dad started, “I’m fine with her running...
caption:
Requested by @eater-of-hopes-and-dreams

“All right, let’s get this over with,” your dad started, “I’m fine with her running around killing ghosts and shit, but you two? Yeah, I’m gonna need more to go on here.” You let out a groan, running a hand over your face as you knew where this was going. The few ways your dad showed he really does care for you.

“I’m sorry?” Sam asked, clearly more confused than Dean was. In fact, Dean seemed to be thinking of how to tell your dad, the famous Tony Stark, that they weren’t interested in you the way Tony thought they were.

“It’s simple, really - is (Y/N) just with you two because she’s nice to look at or is she actually valuable to your…hunting business?” 

“Dad!” you shouted, absolutely mortified at this point. You really wished your dad didn’t have all the money in the world and was able to track you down so easily.

“What? A dad’s gotta ask.” You shot an apologetic look towards the brothers, wishing a hole would just swallow you up right now.

“Look, she’s like a sister to us at this point, and she knows her way around the supernatural. She’s saved our asses more times than I can count. I’ll admit, Sam and I are dicks at times, but we wouldn’t do anything to hurt her. If anything, she’s the one who hurts us. Should’ve seen it that one time I accidentally ate her ice cream. Never again,” Dean explained, finally coming up with something good in that head of his.

A silence swept over the four of you before Tony clapped his hands, nodding. “That’s good enough for me! I mainly just did this for my enjoyment, really. I know if you two tried anything she’d kick your asses before you laid a finger on her. Now, who’s up for some food?”
